<p>Recently wanted to come up with a random keyword. Querying <a href="http://wordnet.princeton.edu/">WordNet</a> and a regular expression did the job.</p>
<p>Installed WordNet on Mac:</p>
<pre><code class="language-{.bash">$ brew install wordnet
</code></pre>
<p>Want a word ending in &quot;esome&quot;?</p>
<pre><code class="language-{.bash">$ wn esome -grepn -grepv -grepa -grepr | egrep -o -e &quot;\w*esome\b&quot; | sort | uniq

adventuresome
awesome
blithesome
bunglesome
cuddlesome
esome
fivesome
gruesome
lithesome
lonesome
lovesome
meddlesome
mettlesome
nettlesome
threesome
tiresome
torturesome
troublesome
unwholesome
venturesome
wholesome
</code></pre>
